Video: Bernadette Wolhuter
The case was remanded to next week for Maliwa to secure a private attorney.
Njabulo and Luyanda disappeared on Tuesday.
READ: 10-year-old Luyanda’s body recovered
The Grade 3 pair was last seen boarding a bus to go home after school.
On Saturday, police recovered Luyanda’s body from dense bush in Montclair, south Durban.
READ: Body of missing boy found
Njabulo’s body was pulled from an area called Grunter’s Gulley, in the Durban harbour on Monday morning.
Njabulo and his best friend disappeared on Thursday, despite initial reports saying that they had last been seen on Tuesday.
Two other suspects have been arrested in connection with the boys’ murders and are expected to appear in court later this week.
